hey driver… HAPPY BIRTHDAY!!🥂🤪
Thank you to everyone who came to celebrate the birthday boy! We love y’all!🫶🏽

A week without my molly girl so I thought I would tell everyone a little bit about her life🤍 Molly was rescued out of a puppy mill in 2006 and we were told she wouldn’t live very long and most likely never walk. She not only overcame being abused and neglected as puppy she thrived and became a service dog and worked in therapy centers with abused children bringing them comfort for 10 years. She was diagnosed with heart failure in 2019 and after being told she only had a couple weeks… lived another 4 years. She was my little miracle. She passed away on 10/31 after having another episode of her heart failure. It only felt right to share this because of how many people loved her over her long and crazy lifetime. Molly has been with me for the past 16 years through every move, life change, friendship… everything. She’s was the kind of dog that everyone instantly loved and called themselves her family. She has been my best friend for as long as I can remember and I was never ready to say goodbye to her. I have never have a met a dog with more love and gentleness to her. She touched the hearts of everyone around her and forever left an imprint on mine. I know she’s in a better place now but I’ll miss her forever. Always take the chance on the rescue dogs they will change your life 🫶🏽 I know many people knew molly from school plays to river trips so I’d appreciate any picture that anyone has of her🤍
2024 you got some big shoes to fill🤍
